{"version":3,"term":{"cols":80,"rows":24,"type":"xterm-kitty"},"timestamp":1782118969,"idle_time_limit":3.0,"command":"bash /tmp/gpu-demo.sh","env":{"SHELL":"/bin/bash"}}
[0.296233, "o", "\r\n\u001b[1;36m━━ BONUS — Multi-tenant GPU on bare metal: HAMi vGPU (slicing, metrics, governance, multi-GPU) ━━\u001b[0m\r\n\r\n\u001b[1;34m2 physical GPUs on srv-t7910 -> HAMi slices them in software (no MIG, no passthrough) with HARD\u001b[0m\r\n"]
[0.000025, "o", "\u001b[1;34mVRAM + compute limits -> each tenant/workload gets isolated, capped, measured slices.\u001b[0m\r\n"]
[2.002018, "o", "\r\n\u001b[1;36m━━ 1/7  The bare-metal GPUs (la GPU del fierro) ━━\u001b[0m\r\n\r\n"]
[0.150753, "o", "  node srv-t7910 advertises nvidia.com/gpu = 20   (Tesla P4 7680MiB + Quadro M4000 8192MiB)\r\n"]
[3.001696, "o", "\r\n\u001b[1;36m━━ 2/7  GOVERNANCE — the GPU budget granted per tenant / namespace ━━\u001b[0m\r\n\r\n\u001b[1;34mWhat each tenant is ALLOWED (hard caps in the pod spec) — the showback / quota view:\u001b[0m\r\n"]
[1.745279, "o", "  NAMESPACE / TENANT          vGPU   VRAM(MiB)   CORES\r\n  ai                             1        6000     80%\r\n  gpu-test                       3       14000     80%\r\n  vcluster-tenant-a-dev          1        1500     15%\r\n"]
[3.032979, "o", "\r\n\u001b[1;36m━━ 3/7  A TENANT's HARD-capped slice (inside its own vCluster) ━━\u001b[0m\r\n\r\n"]
[0.000027, "o", "\u001b[1;34mnvidia-smi from a pod INSIDE vcluster-tenant-a-dev — it sees ONLY its slice of an 8GB card:\u001b[0m\r\n"]
[0.168131, "o", "  |   0  Quadro M4000                   Off |   00000000:03:00.0 Off |                  N/A |\r\n  | 47%   44C    P8             22W /  120W |       0MiB /   1500MiB |      0%      Default |\r\n"]
[0.000409, "o", "\u001b[1;32m  -> capped to 1500MiB. The tenant cannot see or exceed its slice (hard isolation).\u001b[0m\r\n"]
[3.001672, "o", "\r\n\u001b[1;36m━━ 4/7  METRICS — HAMi vGPU telemetry per tenant (the dashboard, in text) ━━\u001b[0m\r\n\r\n"]
[3.103911, "o", "  TENANT (namespace)           LIMIT(MiB)    USED(MiB)\r\n  gpu-test                           6000         2052\r\n  vcluster-tenant-a-dev              1500            0\r\n  physical cards:\r\n"]
[0.000178, "o", "    NVIDIA-Quadro M4000 used = 1304 MiB\r\n    NVIDIA-Tesla P4 used = 1173 MiB\r\n"]
[0.007746, "o", "\u001b[1;34m  (source: hami_vgpu_memory_limit/used_bytes -> Prometheus + Grafana on the cluster)\u001b[0m\r\n"]
[3.002112, "o", "\r\n\u001b[1;36m━━ 5/7  GOVERNANCE enforcement — an over-budget request is rejected (Pending) ━━\u001b[0m\r\n\r\n\u001b[1;34mA tenant asks for 8000MiB (more than any card can give). The scheduler refuses to overcommit:\u001b[0m\r\n"]
[0.127763, "o", "  NAME         READY   STATUS    RESTARTS   AGE     IP       NODE     NOMINATED NODE   READINESS GATES\r\n  gpu-greedy   0/1     Pending   0          6m44s   <none>   <none>   <none>           <none>\r\n"]
[0.159543, "o", "\u001b[1;33m  reason: CardInsufficientMemory(srv-t7910)\u001b[0m\r\n\u001b[1;32m  -> it stays Pending; it cannot starve the tenants that already hold their slices.\u001b[0m\r\n"]
[3.001893, "o", "\r\n\u001b[1;36m━━ 6/7  MULTI-GPU — one pod (Ollama) spanning BOTH physical cards ━━\u001b[0m\r\n\r\n\u001b[1;34mOllama got 2 vGPU (one slice per card, capped 3000MiB each) and spread the model across both:\u001b[0m\r\n"]
[0.30818, "o", "  index, name, memory.used [MiB], memory.total [MiB]\r\n  0, Quadro M4000, 963 MiB, 3000 MiB\r\n  1, Tesla P4, 1090 MiB, 3000 MiB\r\n"]
[0.512471, "o", "  NAME           ID              SIZE      PROCESSOR    CONTEXT    UNTIL              \r\n  llama3.2:1b    baf6a787fdff    2.1 GB    100% GPU     4096       3 minutes from now    \r\n"]
[0.003982, "o", "\u001b[1;32m  -> the model uses VRAM on BOTH the M4000 and the P4, each within its HAMi cap.\u001b[0m\r\n"]
[3.001773, "o", "\r\n\u001b[1;36m━━ 7/7  Ask the LLM (inference live across the sliced GPUs) ━━\u001b[0m\r\n\r\n\u001b[1;34mPrompt: \"Write a short, funny love story between two Kubernetes pods.\"\u001b[0m\r\n"]
[0.000018, "o", "\r\n"]
[6.417254, "o", "  In the bustling Kubernetes ecosystem, \"Pod\" Morgan and \"Node\" Nora locked eyes at the Node \r\n  Manager's conference, where they quickly realized their label was meant to be: \"Scheduling \r\n  Sweethearts\". As they danced around each other in the pods' designated area, they couldn't \r\n  help but restart their love affair with regular meetings and scheduled dates. But little \r\n  did they know, a rogue Container (aka \"Docker\") had been trying to sabotage their romance \r\n  by deploying its own pod-like nemesis – a malicious image labeled as \"Malicious\". Just when \r\n  all hope seemed lost, Morgan and Nora's pods were scheduled for a \"deployment\" of love, and \r\n  they refused to be restarted.\r\n"]
[0.004659, "o", "\r\n"]
[0.000042, "o", "\r\n\u001b[1;36m━━ Real cards -> HAMi-sliced -> hard-capped, measured, quota-enforced, multi-GPU -> live LLM. ━━\u001b[0m\r\n\r\n"]
[1.002642, "x", "0"]
